To verify, ensure that an imaging working instance is running and set the property to stop:

{code}
# euca-modify-property -pservices.imaging.worker.configured=false
{code}

wait a minute, and then check the cloud-error.log for the reported error.

You can manually start the worker using the following if it is not running:

{code}
# euca-modify-property -peuca='com.eucalyptus.imaging.worker.ImagingServiceLaunchers.instance.enable()'
{code}
